Paper: hep-th/9410064

Date: 1994-10-10

Title: QED$_{2+1}$ with Nonzero Fermion Density and Quantum Hall Effect

Authors: Vadim Zeitlin

Comments: 8 pages, LaTeX; FIAN/TD/94-09

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B352 (1995) 422

A general expression for the conductivity in the QED$_{2+1}$ with nonzerofermion density in the uniform magnetic field is derived. It is shown that the$\sigma_{ij}=\varepsilon_{ij}~{\cal C}$ and is a step-function of the chemicalpotential and the magnetic field.